        "uploadsvc/service.go aliases the protocol action/error types directly (`type Action = actions.Action`, `type UnsupportedActionError = actions.UnsupportedActionError`) and again exposes `ParseAction`/`SupportedActions` wrappers.",
        "system/wifi/service/c2c_service.go repeats the same alias+wrapper pattern for C2C (`type C2CAction = actions.Action`, `type UnsupportedC2CActionError = actions.UnsupportedActionError`, `ParseC2CAction`)."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Split this into a clearer boundary: keep protocol/actions as the canonical action-token domain and consume it directly from service packages, or define explicit transport interface contracts in dedicated protocol gateway packages so only one module owns compatibility wrappers and service packages do not replicate pass-through re-exports.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "protocol_actions_boundary_leak"
    }
